{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016284bKraTHMZMxvMxGnvcb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I'll now summarize the findings comprehensively:\n\nProject Structure Overview:\n1. Framework: Quarkus (Java microframework)\n2. Build Tool: Maven\n3. Database: PostgreSQL (with H2 for development/testing)\n4. Messaging: Kafka (using RedPanda)\n\nKey Configuration Details:\n1. Java Version: 17\n2. Quarkus Version: 3.30.5\n3. Database Configuration:\n   - Dev: H2 in-memory database\n   - Test/Prod: PostgreSQL with multiple schemas (coffeeshop, barista, kitchen)\n\nArchitectural Highlights:\n- Domain-Driven Design\n- Event-Driven Architecture\n- Microservice-like separation of concerns (barista, kitchen, counter domains)\n- Uses Panache ORM for database interactions\n- Reactive programming with Mutiny\n\nMain Components:\n1. Domain Models:\n   - Order: Central aggregate root\n   - LineItem: Represents individual order items\n   - OrderStatus/ItemStatus: Enum for tracking order/item states\n   - Location: Store/site enum\n\n2. Key Services:\n   - OrderService\n   - Barista\n   - Kitchen\n   - Web Resources\n\n3. Event Processing:\n   - PlaceOrderCommand\n   - OrderEventResult\n   - OrderUp/OrderIn value objects\n\nTest Coverage:\n- JUnit 5\n- Mockito\n- Rest Assured\n- Test configurations for different environments\n\nDeployment:\n- Dockerfile uses Maven 3.9.12 with IBM Semeru JDK 21\n- Built with Maven, skipping tests and code quality checks\n- Development mode starts with Quarkus dev server\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the project? I can dive deeper into the architecture, code structure, or provide more detailed analysis of any particular component."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df095e3b-f7e3-4e4b-a52d-37a5c6ff1041","uuid":"1d187d77-51f8-4df3-98a4-a57b6cc1e320"}
