{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KSW5bgTSHZiXGofrURACXe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.web;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.counter.api.OrderService;\n     5→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.domain.commands.PlaceOrderCommand;\n     6→import io.vertx.mutiny.core.eventbus.EventBus;\n     7→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n     8→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n     9→\n    10→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    11→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    18→\n    19→@Path(\"/api\")\n    20→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    21→@Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    22→public class CoffeeshopApiResource {\n    23→\n    24→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(CoffeeshopApiResource.class);\n    25→\n    26→    @Inject\n    27→    OrderService orderService;\n    28→\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    EventBus eventBus;\n    31→\n    32→    @POST\n    33→    @Path(\"/order\")\n    34→    @Transactional\n    35→    public Response placeOrder(final PlaceOrderCommand placeOrderCommand) {\n    36→\n    37→        LOGGER.info(\"PlaceOrderCommand received: {}\", placeOrderCommand);\n    38→        orderService.onOrderIn(placeOrderCommand);\n    39→        return Response.accepted().build();\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    @POST\n    43→    @Path(\"/message\")\n    44→    public void sendMessage(final String message) {\n    45→//        webUpdater.send(message);\n    46→        LOGGER.debug(\"received message: {}\", message);\n    47→        LOGGER.debug(\"sending to web-updates: {}\", message);\n    48→        eventBus.publish(\"web-updates\", message);\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→}\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df095e3b-f7e3-4e4b-a52d-37a5c6ff1041","uuid":"407c9cf5-a447-4a8e-8579-10b99bda308a"}
