   data-store-id=\"{storeId}\"\n   954→           data-stream-url=\"{streamUrl}\"\n   955→/>\n   956→<!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->\n   957→<script src=\"https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.7.1/jquery.min.js\"></script>\n   958→<!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->\n   959→<script src=\"js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n   960→<script src=\"js/jquery.matchHeight.js\"></script>\n   961→<script src=\"js/jquery.cookie.js\"></script>\n   962→<script src=\"js/custom.js\"></script>\n   963→<script src=\"js/cafe.js\"></script>\n   964→<script src=\"js/wow.js\"></script>\n   965→<script src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/ekko-lightbox/5.3.0/ekko-lightbox.js\"></script>\n   966→<script src=\"js/toastr.js\"></script>\n   967→<script>\n   968→    new WOW().init();\n   969→</script>\n   970→<script>\n   971→    $(document).on('click', '[data-toggle=\"lightbox\"]', function(event) {\n   972→        event.preventDefault();\n   973→        $(this).ekkoLightbox();\n   974→    });\n   975→</script>\n   976→\n   977→\n   978→</body>\n   979→</html>\n   980→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df095e3b-f7e3-4e4b-a52d-37a5c6ff1041","uuid":"ba86dbc6-678d-4cf8-b44a-60272ae2af54"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SutKeWokrmFA8edETEQ67s","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me update my todo list and begin the migration. The key observations are:\n\n1. **Quarkus-specific features**: Vertx EventBus, Panache ORM, Qute templates, SmallRye Reactive Messaging (Kafka), CDI (@ApplicationScoped, @Inject), JAX-RS (resteasy), Mutiny reactive\n2. **Multiple datasources**: coffeeshop (default), barista, kitchen - all using H2 in dev mode\n3. **Event-driven architecture**: Using Vertx EventBus for internal communication and Kafka for external\n4. **Template**: Qute template with `{storeId}` and `{streamUrl}` placeholders\n\nFor Spring Boot migration, I'll:\n- Replace Panache with Spring Data JPA\n- Replace Vertx EventBus with Spring's ApplicationEventPublisher\n- Replace JAX-RS with Spring Web (RestController)\n- Replace Qute with Thymeleaf\n- Replace SmallRye Kafka with Spring Kafka (but simplify since we need dev mode without Kafka)\n- Use H2 in-memory for dev/testing (single datasource to simplify)\n- Add Spring Boot main application class"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17833,"cache_read_input_tokens":71070,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":17833,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":761},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df095e3b-f7e3-4e4b-a52d-37a5c6ff1041","uuid":"24788ffe-8611-4c24-b48e-ba85dd1405a9"}
